title: Print, "Design for Cartouche with Fountain and Building, in Livre Nouveau Morceaux de Fantaisie (New Book of Works of Fantasy)", 1695–1768
medium: Engraving and etching on laid paper
signed: Signed in plate, lower left: F. de. Cuvilliés. In. et. del.; lower right: CA. de Lespilliez Sc.
inscribed: Inscribed in plate, lower center: C. P. S. C. M.
creditline: Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council
description: Large rocaille formation with building in the background on right. Formation contains water, putti, plants, bow and arrows, and grapevines, leading up to sky where a trellis-like ornament rests with hanging putti.
